(firstQuint)Methylphenidate and Driving Ability in Adult Patients With Attention-Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder.

 This study was set-up to examine the controversial issue whether or not it is safe to drive a car or not when treated with methylphenidate.

 On-the-road driving tests during normal traffic are conducted to determine the effects of methylphenidate versus placebo on driving ability of adult ADHD patients.

In addition, two laboratory tests are conducted to examine memory functioning and inhibitory control.

